<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d289">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Eustis</persName></hi>.</head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-20"><hi rend="italic">September 20,
                                        1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Your instructions cover supply of Mrs. Waller’s reasonable wants as
                                well as passage home. If she desires to see her husband, arrange for
                                visit to prison and access to him in conformity with usual
                                regulations.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>